 withdraw ones lower nature, or at least k=\r\neep it clam and checked c) make a sincere call to God. Only when these thre=\r\ne work together,\n grace descends. And only grace has the power to cause a t=\r\nhorough transformation of a sadhaka. Nothing less. But you can&#39;t demand gra=\r\nce, you can&#39;t beg for grace, you can&#39;t plead, you can&#39;t command, and you ca=\r\nn&#39;t indulge in self-pity. We have to calmly and patiently wait for it for w=\r\nhen the time is right, it calls like a sweet rain on a parched throat, and =\r\nin a flash it can do more than what we can imagine. Basically, we cannot ne=\r\ngotiate with God. Nothing less than a complete honest recoking on what we a=\r\nre, where we are heading, what mistakes lie in our nature is a must.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br=\r\n&gt;Then slowly you will be made to realize the working of a higher Power that=\r\n has nothing to do with your little surface personalities push and pulls ba=\r\nsed on Pavlovian responses to situations incurred over lifetimes. It is thi=\r\ns Power, once understood, that needs to be unquestioningly submitted to in =\r\na progressive manner, while rejecting everything else inside us that pull u=\r\ns in a\n different direction and wants to hang on to our earlier flawed pers=\r\nonality. Long, long, long road. Patience is a key.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp; *&n=\r\nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;A few general thoughts on Purusacharana since there wer=\r\ne a few mails on this topic. Again, just my opinion. Feel free to reject it=\r\n if needed.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Start with the word. Purusha+acharana. Behaving like a m=\r\nan. And what does it mean? Some may say it means being brave, being mentall=\r\ny robust, being aggressive, or being commanding etc. All these are terms th=\r\nat are often used in colloquial language to indicate a proverbial &#39;manly&#39; b=\r\nehavior. But in sadhana, Purusha is a different concept. Looking inwards an=\r\nd separating a part of your being, from the mind, from your thoughts, from =\r\nyour emotions, and even from your physcial nature. This part of your being =\r\nwill only stand back and watch, as silent witness, and then either give or =\r\nreject consent to various movements of your lower nature (lust, anger,\n jea=\r\nlousy, greed, covetousness, ETC). Once this is firmly installed in your sys=\r\ntem - this Purusha - it will be able to stop and clam down various parts of=\r\n your being which have the tendency to leap-up in joy (sukha) or get deflat=\r\ned (dukhkha) at surface appearances and shallow understandings. This is how=\r\n a Purusha works in Yoga. When this kind of Purusha consciounsess is instal=\r\nled and established, an expansion of the mind happens beyond the rational, =\r\nthe emotional or even the physical nature/consciousness.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;After this =\r\nbasic step has been done properly, then the sadhana of purushacharana is to=\r\n be done. By this method, a progressive 1/10 numerical deduction in the sad=\r\nhana is done for each element. That is for 1000 japas, 100 homas, 10 tarpan=\r\na, 1 marjana and finally feeding people. Each of this will affect a realiza=\r\ntion of the mantra is each of the layers - in reverse order from annamaya-k=\r\nosha, to pranamaya-kosha, to manomaya-kosha to vigyanmaya-kosha\n (the spiri=\r\ntual layers beyond and above the reasoning mind). THAT is the perfect effec=\r\nt of a spotless purushacharana. That is mantra siddhi and mantra chaitanya.=\r\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;While doing a purushacharana, tremenodus amount of obstacles will c=\r\nome in the path of the sadhaka. To overcome these, while sticking to the ex=\r\nacting rules of the sadhana, one MUST have done the first step properly, th=\r\nat is installed a Purusha consciousness in his/her system, one that is unsh=\r\nakeable in any adverse conditions. One that is perfectly unmoved by the wor=\r\nking of the lower nature in man as well as outside man. For example, one ma=\r\ny get affected by high fever, various crisis situations, various attacks fr=\r\nom hostile forces etc etc, Many things. But inspite of that the Purusha con=\r\nsciouness, if it has been firmly established, will drive the sadhana withou=\r\nt a glitch, remaining unmoved. Of course, one must honestly judge how far s=\r\nuch a consciousness has been developed. Self-delusion has\n to be guarded ag=\r\nainst.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;One can try for oneself to do purushacharanas and see how far=\r\n one succeeds. In my opinion though, 98 % of seekers in this age are unfit =\r\nto do purushacharana and succeed in this sadhana. For the Purusha conscious=\r\nness has not been established in the system by most people. In the last 6 y=\r\nears among all varieties of sadhakas I have met, of various paths, only two=\r\n were there who I felt can pull off a genuine purusacharana. Rest no chance=\r\n.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Doing any sadhana at the same time, same place, using same materia=\r\nls, without breaks for years and years is always good. Goes without saying.=\r\n This too, most people cannot do flawlessly. Purushacharana is far more com=\r\nplex and demanding. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Then the other option is to develop genuine sur=\r\nrender from the deepest part of your heart. Do sadhana, and wait patiently.=\r\n Her grace is bound to come and illuminate the path. Meanhile, we can keep =\r\nworking on rectifying the lower nature in\n ourselves.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Jai Ma Tara.&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Regards&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;Rajarshi&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;di=\r\nv&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;div class=3D&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span c=\r\nlass=3D&quot;Apple-style-span&quot; style=3D&quot;font-size:16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class=3D&quot;Apple=\r\n-style-span&quot; style=3D&quot;color:rgb(153, 153, 153);&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;